---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Animation Guide - Hovue"
  description="Learn how to use animations with Hovue icons. Explore all available animation types and how to customize them."
  prev={{ url: '/docs/api', title: 'API Reference' }}
  next={{ url: '/docs/examples', title: 'Examples Gallery' }}
>
  <h1>Animation Guide</h1>

  <p>
    Hovue icons come with built-in animations that bring your interface to life. This guide covers
    all available animation types and how to customize them.
  </p>

  <h2>Animation Types</h2>

  <p>Hovue supports five animation types, each designed for different use cases:</p>

  <h3>Slide</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>slide</code> animation moves the icon in a direction. Perfect for arrows and navigation
    elements.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"slide"</span
    ><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span
      style="color: var(--cyan);">"300"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>Bounce</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>bounce</code> animation creates a playful bounce effect. Great for success states and attention-grabbing
    elements.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoCheck</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"bounce"</span
    ><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span
      style="color: var(--cyan);">"400"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>Rotate</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>rotate</code> animation spins the icon. Ideal for loading states and refresh indicators.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoRefresh</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"rotate"</span
    ><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span
      style="color: var(--cyan);">"1000"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>Pulse</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>pulse</code> animation creates a subtle pulsing effect. Perfect for notifications and alerts.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoBell</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"pulse"</span
    ><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span
      style="color: var(--cyan);">"1500"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>Fade</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>fade</code> animation creates a smooth fade in/out effect. Great for transitions and state
    changes.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoHeart</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"fade"</span
    ><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span
      style="color: var(--cyan);">"500"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h2>Animation Duration</h2>

  <p>
    Control the speed of animations using the <code>animation-duration</code> prop. Duration is specified
    in milliseconds.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// Fast animation (200ms)</span><br />
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"200"</span
    > /&gt;<br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// Medium animation (300ms - default)</span><br />
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"300"</span
    > /&gt;<br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// Slow animation (600ms)</span><br />
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"600"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h2>Triggering Animations</h2>

  <h3>On Hover</h3>
  <p>Animations can be triggered on hover by default:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"slide"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>On Click</h3>
  <p>Trigger animations programmatically on click:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoRefresh</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"rotate"</span
    ><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">@click</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"triggerAnimation"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>Conditional Animations</h3>
  <p>Use animations conditionally based on state:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoLoader</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation</span>=<span
      style="color: var(--cyan);">"isLoading ? 'rotate' : 'none'"</span
    ><br />
    /&gt;
  </div>

  <h2>Best Practices</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Use appropriate animations:</strong> Match animation types to the icon's purpose (e.g.,
      rotate for loaders, slide for arrows).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Keep durations reasonable:</strong> 200-600ms is usually ideal. Too fast feels jarring,
      too slow feels sluggish.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Don't overuse:</strong> Too many animated icons can be distracting. Use animations strategically.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Consider accessibility:</strong> Respect <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> when possible.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <p>Check out the <a href="/docs/examples">Examples Gallery</a> to see animations in action.</p>
</DocsLayout>
